methods.name: Constructor
methods.description: Constructs a new container from a variety of data sources, optionally using a user supplied allocator alloc.

params.name: alloc
params.descripton: allocator to use for all memory allocations of this container

params.name: count
params.descripton: the size of the container

params.name: value
params.descripton: the value to initialize elements of the container with

params.name: first
params.descripton: the range to copy the elements from

params.name: last
params.descripton: another container to be used as source to initialize the elements of the container with

params.name: other
params.descripton: initializer list to initialize the elements of the container with

returns.description: The vector constructed by the constructor.

methods.name: operator[]
methods.description: Returns a reference to the element at specified location pos. No bounds checking is performed.

params.name: pos
params.description: position of the element to return

params.name: value
params.description: The value of the element to append.

returns.description: Pointer to the underlying element storage. For non-empty containers, the returned pointer compares equal to the address of the first element.
